get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">  sued Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s parents</a>=
, Stanford Law School professors Joseph Bankman and Barbara Fried, for, let=
=E2=80=99s say, being the knowing beneficiaries of FTX=E2=80=99s largesse. =
Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32765671.2=
58423/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL=
3JyYktPcElqcktONC92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBacb38087" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the compl=
aint</a>. When FTX was cheerfully flinging around money on luxury housing a=
nd=C2=A0private jets and political donations and Super Bowl ads, Bankman an=
d Fried allegedly got themselves some luxury housing:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On or about February 11, 2022, Ban=
kman and Fried signed an agreement to purchase a $16.4 million 30,000 squar=
e-foot luxury property (for the two of them) with unobstructed ocean views =
in the Old Fort Bay community in The Bahamas, referred to as =E2=80=9CBlue =
Water=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9COld Fort Bay.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6 Neither Bankman=
 nor Fried contributed any money of their own towards the purchase of Blue =
