<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A general theory of art might be that artists =
create cultural cachet, and art collectors have cash, and the collectors tr=
ade their cash for the artists=E2=80=99 cachet. For centuries the main form=
 of cultural=C2=A0cachet that artists could create was pretty pictures that=
 looked nice hanging in collectors=E2=80=99 dining rooms and impressed thei=
r dinner guests, and so the prettier the pictures were the more they were w=
orth.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But eventually it got fairly easy=C2=A0to get =
pictures of arbitrary prettiness, so pretty pictures do not carry the cache=
t and distinction that they once did, so collectors are not willing to pay =
that much for them. Collectors want more abstract and complicated forms of =
cultural cachet. They want their art to convey=C2=A0<em>sophistication</em>=
, and one very popular way to convey sophistication is by showing that you =
are in some sense=C2=A0<em>in on the joke</em>. If you bought Duchamp=E2=80=
=99s urinal, that showed that you were with it.<a class=3D"footnote-index" =
href=3D"#footnote-9" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: =
inline-block;">
<span>[9]</span>
